TLINE.TDLINE: &CAUSE&
An error occurred when creating the Batch Input Session.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The program terminates. No banks have been changed.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
Analyse the error message immediately above this message in the log.
Retry once the cause for the error has been removed.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
The program was set to automatically run the Batch Input session which
updates the bank master table. Since there was a fatal error during the
file processing, the Batch Input session is not executed.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The Batch Input session has been created, but will not be executed
automatically.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
The Batch Input session should be deleted. It can be recreated after the
fatal error has been solved.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
The split program supports a maximum of 999 target files.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The processing is aborted after creating 999 target files.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
Rerun the split with an increased block size to lower the number of
target files necessary.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
This message contains statistical information.
The number of bank entries that were not processed, because there was an
error in the data or the processing of the data. The relevant error
message(s) can be found in the application log.
The number of bank entries that were not processed because they did not
match the selection criteria. This includes the program parameters from
the selection screen as well as customising settings.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
If any errors are indicated, check the log for further detail.
If you want to load all banks from the GPF file, the country settings
must be for external bank key assignment and the Accuity unique bank key
must be used.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
An error was encountered in program ZACC_GPFXML_LOAD when initialising
the iXML Library interface. The error message indicates which step has
failed.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The program is terminated.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
Investigate the error with a developer or system administrator.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
The iXML Library has reported one or more syntactical errors that were
encountered while parsing the XML file. The location of the error and
the error message is mentioned below this message.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The program aborts processing. Any Batch Input data that has already
been prepared should not be used and the Batch Input session deleted
without executing it.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
1. Delete the Batch Input session for the bank update if any was
created.
2. Verify with your Accuity contact why the file was in error. Provide
the error message(s) listed below this message to enable a diagnosis.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
This message contains the number of banks that are still used by vendor
or customer master records. If this is greater than 0, action needs to
be taken to amend the vendor or customer bank data.
If the parameter 'Only delete unused banks' is chosen, these banks will
not be deleted.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
If deleted banks are still in use and the option to log these banks has
been activated, you will find the relevant bank codes in this log.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
The program encountered a fatal error during processing. The error is
indicated in the application log above.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The program confirms that it has terminated due to a fatal error.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
If a batch input session was created, delete this and do not run any of
the transactions.
Check the error message above on how to resolve the error before you
retry.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
The bank entry read from the file is missing one or more of the
following mandatory elements.
Bank country
Bank key
Bank name
Swift BIC and local clearing code
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The bank entry is not processed. Processing continues with the next
entry.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
Verify the file you are trying to load with your Accuity contact. It
seems to be corrupted.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
The load program expects the GPF file to indicate the action on the
bank. The action identified was not one of the following valid codes.
A - Add bank
M - Modify bank
D - Delete bank
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The current bank entry is marked as erroneous and processing is skipped.
The program continues processing with the next bank entry.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
Verify the file you are trying to load with your Accuity contact. It
seems to be corrupted.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
The program has tried to establish the SAP country code for the ISO
country code mentioned. It has found several matching entries in the
country customising.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The processing of this bank entry is skipped.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
Ensure that the ISO country code is linked to one country only. You can
maintain the country properties in the IMG or via view maintenance for
view V_T005.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
The program has tried to establish the SAP country code for the ISO
country code mentioned. It has not found a matching entry in the country
customising. To establish the country code, the program analyses;
The SAP country directory (table T005)
An additional mapping table ZACC_MAP that assigns territories with their
own ISO code to a parent country, for instance GG (Guernsey) to GB
(Great Britain).
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The processing of this bank entry is skipped.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
Please verify if the ISO country code is a valid code. If yes, update
your country setup with the ISO code. You can do this in the IMG or via
view maintenance for view V_T005 for sovereign countries or via table
ZACC_MAP for territories.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
The program has encountered a bank key type that is not supported.
The load program supports the bank key types 1 (bank code), 3 (internal
assignment), and 4 (external assignment) for banks. Specifically, the
obsolete bank key type 2 (bank data per account) is not supported with
the Accuity GPF file.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The bank entry is not processed. Processing is continued with the next
bank entry.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
Verify your customising settings for the given country.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
In the above country, internal number assignment is used for bank master
maintenance. In this mode, the load program tries to establish the bank
key via the domestic bank code or the Swift BIC.
It requires an exact match of either one bank master or one undeleted
bank master. In the current case, multiple bank masters were found.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The program skips this bank entry and continues processing with the
next.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
Ensure that you have only one active bank entry for the said bank.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
The program checks the formal integrity of the Swift BIC loaded from the
XML file. For the current bank entry the Swift BIC is not correct.
If a Swift BIC is provided with the bank record, the Swift BIC must be;
eight or eleven characters long
pertain to the current country or one of its territories as per table
ZACC_MAP or
pertain to a country specified in table ZACC_BIC.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The program skips the processing of the bank entry and proceeds with the
next.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
This error may indicate a corrupt source file. Please verify with your
Accuity contact.
Please note that if this message is indicated as a warning instead of an
error, the impacted bank entry was marked for deletion. Probably, no
action is required for these cases.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
The above bank has been indicated as obsolete by Accuity data. It is
still being used within vendor or customer master records, though. It
will be marked for deletion unless parameter is set to only delete
unused banks.
The vendor or customer number cited is one occurrence where the bank has
been found in use. It may not be the only vendor or customer where the
bank is used. The test run list will show all vendors / customers at the
bottom.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
A warning is issued if requested.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
Update the relevant vendor and customer master records with the correct
bank data.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
The given field is too long in the input data and needs to be truncated.
The check is made on fields such as the name and street of the bank.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
A warning is issued and the field value is truncated to avoid processing
errors in Batch Input.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
The bank data should typically be usable without restrictions. If
problems occur, please contact your Accuity representative about the
possibility of shortening the name or address data.
Please note that a longer value for the street name can be supported, if
central address management (CAM) is used. The street name can then be up
to 60 characters. Only 35 characters are supported within the bank
master data.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
When the option "Full initial file load" is selected, the existing bank
master records are checked against the GPF file. Any bank not mentioned
in the file is marked for deletion.
The bank master check will take the bank data selection into account.
The bank matching is done according to the bank key settings. If the
option is activated, deleted banks that are still in use will be listed
in the log.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The message warns the user about the handling of full uploads.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
If the described handling is requested, confirm your selection with <(>
<<)>Enter>.
If you do not want to delete bank master records not present in the GPF
file, select the "Partial initial file load" option instead.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
In full initial load mode, the program matches existing banks against
the GPF file data. No banks have been found in the SAP bank master that
match the selection.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
This fact is logged for information only.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
No action is required.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
In full initial load mode, the program verifies the existing banks
against the Accuity GPF file, which contains all banks. Any bank not
found in the file is marked for deletion.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The number of banks not found in the file is reported for information
only.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
If there are any banks still in use in vendor or customer master records
and the option to log these has been activated, the log will contain the
banks to be investigated after this message.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
The region code &4 given in tag <COUNTRYCSP> from the XML
file could not be mapped to a valid Region in SAP.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The address details of the bank will be added / updated without the
Region.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
Add the missing region code in customising (SAP NetWeaver -> General
Settings -> Set Countries -> Insert Regions), table T005S
or link the region code from the XML file to an existing Region in SAP
using table ZACC_REGI.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
The function module &V1& was assigned as an exit function to country
&V2& or to all countries. It cannot be found in the function module
library.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The user exit function is ignored and bank processing proceeds without
calling the function.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
The bank records are loaded as if there was no user exit function
assigned.
If special handling is required, please develop a function module based
on Z_ACC_GPF_USER_EXIT_TEMPLATE and assign it to the relevant country
(or all countries) in table ZACC_EXIT.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
For local language import, you need to specify an address version in
which to store the address information. For country &V1& no address
version could be established.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The import of the current bank record is skipped.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
Please define the target address version for the country in table
ZACC_LOCAL_LANG. You can set a target address version for a specific
country, or use a default setting associated with country = space. If
both entries have been maintained, the country-specific address version
is used.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
You have assigned the default address version (space) to bank country
&V1&. The default address version is maintained during the normal bank
data import. In local language import mode, only other active address
version may be selected.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The import of the current bank record is skipped.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
Please assign a different target address version in table
ZACC_LOCAL_LANG.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
Target address version &V4& for bank country &V1& has not been defined
or activated.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The import of the current bank record is skipped.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
Please activate the address version in view V_SAPTSADV or assign a
different target address version in table ZACC_LOCAL_LANG.
&SYS_ADMIN&
&CAUSE&
Local language import only adds further address information to an
existing bank. Bank &V1& &V2& has not been created in SAP.
&SYSTEM_RESPONSE&
The bank record is skipped.
&WHAT_TO_DO&
Please import the associated GPF initial of update file first, then load
the local language data in a second step.
You can also import the local language data file in normal import mode
to create the bank. Then the address data is stored in the default
address version, however, not the one specified for local language data
import.
&SYS_ADMIN&
